<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n14157c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n14" href="#n14157c">N14 (VI.B.7)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n14all.htm#n14157c"> 157(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Logberg / ropes</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">All laws to be valid must be promulgated from the Tynwald Hill which corresponds to the <mark><i>l&ouml;gberg</i></mark> or law-hill of the Icelandic <i>althing</i>. When the court is held the coroner &lsquo;fences&rsquo; it against all disturbance or disorder, just as in the old Norwegian <i>Gulathing</i> we hear of <i>v&eacute;-b&ouml;nd</i> or <mark>sanctuary-ropes</mark> drawn around the assembly. <small> Allen Mawer, <a name="AMTV1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#AMTV1"><cite title="source">The Vikings</cite></a>, (1913) 116</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
